# Testing Enforcement

## The Rule

Every change to a production file in `src/**/*.{ts,tsx}` MUST include a corresponding `*.test.*` update. Tests are part of the definition of done.

**Excluded:** `src/test-utils/**`, `src/components/ui/**`, `src/vitest.d.ts`.

## When Tests Must Be Written

| Scenario | Action |
|----------|--------|
| New file created | Create co-located `*.test.tsx` |
| Existing file modified | Update the corresponding test file |
| New branch/condition added | Add test case for the new branch |
| Bug fix | Add regression test |
| File deleted | Delete the corresponding test file |

## Coverage Gate

100% branch + 100% line coverage enforced in `vitest.config.ts`. Run `npm run test:coverage` to verify.

## Test Co-Location

Tests live next to the file they test:
```
src/components/auth/
├── auth-form.tsx
├── auth-form.test.tsx
```

## Anti-Patterns (Forbidden)

- `test.skip()` / `test.todo()` in committed code
- `toMatchSnapshot()` — use explicit assertions
- Empty `waitFor(() => {})` — always assert inside
- Duplicating global mocks from `setup.ts` (override only when needed)

## Test Naming

`it("should show empty state when user has no invites", ...)` — always scenario + outcome. Never `it("works")`.
